SupportingEvidence: The proliferation score is low (0.214), indicating a slow-growing tumor which is consistent with the fetal subtype.
The stemness score is also low (0.193), suggesting the cells are more differentiated, a characteristic of the fetal subtype.

The prognostic score is high (1.000), indicating a poor prognosis. This could be due to other factors such as tumor location or size, not necessarily the subtype.
